CONTROLLING RESOURCE ORDER WITH EXPLICIT DEPENDENCIES : 

depends-on Meta-arguments: ensures resources are created in the right order.
Explicitly define dependencies: terraform may not automatically know about dependencies needed for your deployment.
Ensure correct provisioning order
depends_on = [aws_db_instance.db]

lifecycle meta-argument : controlling how terraform manages resources
-Customise how terraform manage resources
-You can protect resources or avoid changes
-uses lifecycle block inside of your resource : options include prevent_destroy, create_before_destroy and ignore_changes
-replace_triggered_by : Force resource replacement when specified resources or attributes change. Useful for dependencies that don't trigger automatic replacement.
-precondition and postcondition : Validate resource state before and after operation. Advance validation for complex deployments.

EXAMPLES :
lifecycle {
    ignore_changes = [vm_size]
  }
  -----
  lifecycle {
    create_before_destroy = true
  }
--------
lifecycle {
    replace_triggered_by = [aws_security_group.web]
  }
-------
lifecycle {
    precondition {
      condition = var.vm_size != "Basic_A0"
      error_message = "Basic_A0 is deprecated"
  }
}








